# Testing
- Add regression tests for fixed bugs and feature tests for business workflows.
- Test success, validation failure, authorization failure, invalid state transitions, and important integration failures.
- Keep unit tests for isolated calculation or transformation logic; prefer feature tests for Laravel wiring.
- Use factories/builders and avoid dependence on execution order or shared database state.
- Mock external boundaries, not core domain behavior.
- Assert persisted state and side effects, not only HTTP status.
- For payment/webhook flows, test duplicate delivery and retry behavior.
- Run the narrow relevant suite first, then broader suites when practical.
